product_name: L'OrealColour Riche Intense Volume Matte Lipstick
summary: SummaryDiscover L'Oreal's powdery Colour Riche Intense Volume Matte Lipstick that lasts for up to 16hrs. Infused with hyaluronic acid, this lipstick leaves lips feeling comfortable and looking fuller all day long.
details: DetailsFeaturesDiscover the powdery matte lipstick that lasts for up to 16hr. All day matte finish that does not look flatSlim bullet for precise application. Can be used to line your lips for contour or fill your lips with intense matte color.Color that doesn't smudge, bleed, migrate or feather.Available in multiple saturated shades that flatter a variety of skin tones. Find your shade today.BenefitsInfused with hyaluronic acid. Lips feel comfortable and look fuller all day long.Item 2616884How To UseApply starting in the center of your upper lip. Work from the center to outer edges of your lips, following the contour of your mouth. Then glide across the entire bottom lip.IngredientsLe Nude Unstoppable: Dimethicone, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Phenyl Trimethicone, Tridecyl Trimellitate, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Hydrogenated Jojoba Oil, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Isostearyl Isostearate, Kaolin, Paraffin, Isohexadecane, Nylon-12, Vinyl Dimethicone/Methicone Silsesquioxane Crosspolymer, Cera Microcristallina/Microcrystalline Wax/Cire Microcristalline, Polyethylene, Synthetic Wax, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil, Triethoxysilylethyl Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Vanillin, Alumina, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Serica Powder/Silk Powder/Poudre De Soie, Perlite, Vanilla Planifolia Fruit Extract, Trihydroxystearin, Calcium Sodium Borosilicate, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Magnesium Silicate, Silica, Sodium Hyaluronate, Tocopherol, Tin Oxide, Glucomannan. May Contain (+/-): Ci 77491, Ci 77492, Ci 77499/Iron Oxides, Ci 77891/Titanium Dioxide, Mica, Ci 15850/Red 7, Ci 45410/Red 28 Lake, Ci 19140/Yellow 5 Lake, Ci 42090/Blue 1 Lake, Ci 15985/Yellow 6 Lake, Ci 45380/Red 22 Lake. (F.I.L. N70027290/1).
how_to_use: Apply starting in the center of your upper lip. Work from the center to outer edges of your lips, following the contour of your mouth. Then glide across the entire bottom lip.

reviews.comments: Though I loved the color, I was looking for lip color that would didn't need to be reapplied after eating, drinking or hours later after applying.

reviews.headline: I would definitely buy this product again
reviews.comments: Decided to give this lipstick a try because of a review video I saw. I tried to find WORTH IT MEDIUM satin lipstick but it was out of stock so I decided to give the 601 WORTH IT matte lipstick and so glad I did. It's a beautiful pink/mauve color.

reviews.headline: Unusable
reviews.comments: This was unusable and all stuck inside the cap.  I have had medical issues and have not been back to return it.

reviews.headline: Wore it On my Wedding Day
reviews.comments:
I thoroughly enjoy how pigmented this is. It has a smooth application. Its giving smooth matte. (Make sure to exfoliate your lips, it can emphasize hanging lip skin.) The price is decent. The formula is light and airy. Its like you are not wearing anything. 

For this specific pigment though, Le Plum Dominant, its not my favorite. The final look is good, but the deliverance when applying, it can be off putting. It has a strong floral scent. If you accidentally get it into your mouth, you can taste the scent. Its not transferproof. If you are someone who talks alot, you will need to reapply. 

Personally, I like the Le Nude Assertive. The scent on that one is not strong.

reviews.headline: Pleasantly Surprised
reviews.comments: I wasn't looking for lipstick, just something to get me free shipping. I liked all the color options and knew I needed a brown. I ordered 137 Le Nude Assertive. It went on smooth and the color popped. I immediately loved it. Not tacky, little transfer.

reviews.headline: Ok, not long lasting
reviews.comments: The color range is very nice and overall it's a ok matte lipstick. These were on sale, so I purchased several colors try in rose/mauve. The lasting power isn't long (applied a Mac primer) as I had to reply after eating (something I never have to do with my Nars liquid lipstick), but given the price point & pretty color range and sleek, compact case size, I'm keeping them and would recommend, knowing I'll have to do touch-ups.

reviews.headline: Love it!

reviews.headline: unique
reviews.comments: lipstick is kinda my hobby and I have many, but this is a new favorite--especially 113....a color that is flattering but goes with anything. The packaging looks and feels so elegant and I don't think there's anything out there quite like this. Goes on easily, a snap to fix mistakes, feels wonderful on the lips. The slimness makes it foolproof to apply. I don't consider it volumizing or longwear but it's such a pleasure to apply, who cares? Absolutely love it!

reviews.headline: I love this lipstick!!
reviews.comments: This is an amazing drugstore lipstick! It is MAC quality for a more affordable price! I bought the medium blue based red, and I love it! Highly Recommend!

reviews.headline: I'm shook!

faceoff_positive.comments: This matte L'Oreal Paris Colour Riche Intense Volume is a great buildable color for every day use. it glides on smooth and the matte finish is really forgiving on my skin. The color I have is Le Wood Nonchalant and I would say after a few times using it it is a bit deeper of a shade than I am used to, but still really beautiful. I do love that I choose how rich the color is on my skin since it is buildable. I typically use less product than more and it is nice I have this option with this lip color. Compared to other matte lip colors I've used this is really great and a similar application. The top of the product stays on really well too, I feel comfortable traveling with it and throwing it in my bag without worrying. This is a super practical product and I would recommend others to try it out. It is nice that there are a lot of shades to try from and I think next time I buy this I will try another shade, maybe Le Nude Independent. I do like the matte texture of the product as it is very easy to use. Overall I am happy using this lip color.
faceoff_positive.headline: Buildable matte lip color

faceoff_negative.comments: The packaging was cute! The color was ok, but not a color I'd choose for myself. It was too coral-y for my liking. It was definitely not transfer proof and had a stain finish to it. It wasn't a true matte. It was lightweight and comfortable though.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not Transfer Proof
